<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge led public tributes to Prince Harry on his 36th birthday.  </p>

<p>Prince William and Kate Middleton shared a throwback snap of Harry beating them both in a running race at a joint public engagement in 2017, alongside the simple caption: 'Wishing a very happy birthday to Prince Harry today!' </p>

<p>The Queen, 94, and Prince Charles, 71, shared their own social media tributes, with each choosing photos of Harry laughing at public engagements.   </p>

<p>Prince Harry will celebrate his birthday with wife Meghan Markle and their son Archie in Santa Barbara, where they recently bought their first US home.  </p>

<p> </p>

